  55     """The package was not found."""

  58 class EntryPoint(
  59         PyPy_repr,
  60         collections.namedtuple('EntryPointBase', 'name value group')):
  61     """An entry point as defined by Python packaging conventions.
  62 
  63     See `the packaging docs on entry points
  64     <https://packaging.python.org/specifications/entry-points/>`_
  65     for more information.
  66     """
  67 
  68     pattern = re.compile(
  69         r'(?P<module>[\w.]+)\s*'
  70         r'(:\s*(?P<attr>[\w.]+))?\s*'
  71         r'(?P<extras>\[.*\])?\s*$'
  72         )
  73     """
  74     A regular expression describing the syntax for an entry point,
  75     which might look like:
  76 
  77         - module
  78         - package.module
  79         - package.module:attribute
  80         - package.module:object.attribute
  81         - package.module:attr [extra1, extra2]
  82 
  83     Other combinations are possible as well.
  84 
  85     The expression is lenient about whitespace around the ':',
  86     following the attr, and following any extras.
  87     """
  88 
  89     def load(self):
  90         """Load the entry point from its definition. If only a module
  91         is indicated by the value, return that module. Otherwise,
  92         return the named object.
  93         """
  94         match = self.pattern.match(self.value)
  95         module = import_module(match.group('module'))
  96         attrs = filter(None, (match.group('attr') or '').split('.'))
  97         return functools.reduce(getattr, attrs, module)
  98 
  99     @property
 100     def module(self):
 101         match = self.pattern.match(self.value)
 102         return match.group('module')
 103 
 104     @property
 105     def attr(self):
 106         match = self.pattern.match(self.value)
 107         return match.group('attr')
 108 
 109     @property
 110     def extras(self):
 111         match = self.pattern.match(self.value)
 112         return list(re.finditer(r'\w+', match.group('extras') or ''))
 113 
 114     @classmethod
 115     def _from_config(cls, config):
 116         return [
 117             cls(name, value, group)
 118             for group in config.sections()
 119             for name, value in config.items(group)
 120             ]
 121 
 122     @classmethod
 123     def _from_text(cls, text):
 124         config = ConfigParser(delimiters='=')
 125         # case sensitive: https://stackoverflow.com/q/1611799/812183
 126         config.optionxform = str
 127         try:
 128             config.read_string(text)
 129         except AttributeError:  # pragma: nocover
 130             # Python 2 has no read_string
 131             config.readfp(io.StringIO(text))
 132         return EntryPoint._from_config(config)
 133 
 134     def __iter__(self):
 135         """
 136         Supply iter so one may construct dicts of EntryPoints easily.
 137         """
 138         return iter((self.name, self))
 139 
 140     def __reduce__(self):
 141         return (
 142             self.__class__,
 143             (self.name, self.value, self.group),
 144             )

 147 class PackagePath(pathlib.PurePosixPath):
 148     """A reference to a path in a package"""
 149 
 150     def read_text(self, encoding='utf-8'):
 151         with self.locate().open(encoding=encoding) as stream:
 152             return stream.read()
 153 
 154     def read_binary(self):
 155         with self.locate().open('rb') as stream:
 156             return stream.read()
 157 
 158     def locate(self):
 159         """Return a path-like object for this path"""
 160         return self.dist.locate_file(self)
 161 
 162 
 163 class FileHash:
 164     def __init__(self, spec):
 165         self.mode, _, self.value = spec.partition('=')
 166 
 167     def __repr__(self):
 168         return '<FileHash mode: {} value: {}>'.format(self.mode, self.value)

 171 class Distribution:
 172     """A Python distribution package."""
 173 
 174     @abc.abstractmethod
 175     def read_text(self, filename):
 176         """Attempt to load metadata file given by the name.
 177 
 178         :param filename: The name of the file in the distribution info.
 179         :return: The text if found, otherwise None.
 180         """
 181 
 182     @abc.abstractmethod
 183     def locate_file(self, path):
 184         """
 185         Given a path to a file in this distribution, return a path
 186         to it.
 187         """
 188 
 189     @classmethod
 190     def from_name(cls, name):
 191         """Return the Distribution for the given package name.
 192 
 193         :param name: The name of the distribution package to search for.
 194         :return: The Distribution instance (or subclass thereof) for the named
 195             package, if found.
 196         :raises PackageNotFoundError: When the named package's distribution
 197             metadata cannot be found.
 198         """
 199         for resolver in cls._discover_resolvers():
 200             dists = resolver(DistributionFinder.Context(name=name))
 201             dist = next(dists, None)
 202             if dist is not None:
 203                 return dist
 204         else:
 205             raise PackageNotFoundError(name)
 206 
 207     @classmethod
 208     def discover(cls, **kwargs):
 209         """Return an iterable of Distribution objects for all packages.
 210 
 211         Pass a ``context`` or pass keyword arguments for constructing
 212         a context.
 213 
 214         :context: A ``DistributionFinder.Context`` object.
 215         :return: Iterable of Distribution objects for all packages.
 216         """
 217         context = kwargs.pop('context', None)
 218         if context and kwargs:
 219             raise ValueError("cannot accept context and kwargs")
 220         context = context or DistributionFinder.Context(**kwargs)
 221         return itertools.chain.from_iterable(
 222             resolver(context)
 223             for resolver in cls._discover_resolvers()
 224             )
 225 
 226     @staticmethod
 227     def at(path):
 228         """Return a Distribution for the indicated metadata path
 229 
 230         :param path: a string or path-like object
 231         :return: a concrete Distribution instance for the path
 232         """
 233         return PathDistribution(pathlib.Path(path))
 234 
 235     @staticmethod
 236     def _discover_resolvers():
 237         """Search the meta_path for resolvers."""
 238         declared = (
 239             getattr(finder, 'find_distributions', None)
 240             for finder in sys.meta_path
 241             )
 242         return filter(None, declared)
 243 
 244     @property
 245     def metadata(self):
 246         """Return the parsed metadata for this Distribution.
 247 
 248         The returned object will have keys that name the various bits of
 249         metadata.  See PEP 566 for details.
 250         """
 251         text = (
 252             self.read_text('METADATA')
 253             or self.read_text('PKG-INFO')
 254             # This last clause is here to support old egg-info files.  Its
 255             # effect is to just end up using the PathDistribution's self._path
 256             # (which points to the egg-info file) attribute unchanged.
 257             or self.read_text('')
 258             )
 259         return email_message_from_string(text)
 260 
 261     @property
 262     def version(self):
 263         """Return the 'Version' metadata for the distribution package."""
 264         return self.metadata['Version']
 265 
 266     @property
 267     def entry_points(self):
 268         return EntryPoint._from_text(self.read_text('entry_points.txt'))
 269 
 270     @property
 271     def files(self):
 272         """Files in this distribution.
 273 
 274         :return: List of PackagePath for this distribution or None
 275 
 276         Result is `None` if the metadata file that enumerates files
 277         (i.e. RECORD for dist-info or SOURCES.txt for egg-info) is
 278         missing.
 279         Result may be empty if the metadata exists but is empty.
 280         """
 281         file_lines = self._read_files_distinfo() or self._read_files_egginfo()
 282 
 283         def make_file(name, hash=None, size_str=None):
 284             result = PackagePath(name)
 285             result.hash = FileHash(hash) if hash else None
 286             result.size = int(size_str) if size_str else None
 287             result.dist = self
 288             return result
 289 
 290         return file_lines and list(starmap(make_file, csv.reader(file_lines)))
 291 
 292     def _read_files_distinfo(self):
 293         """
 294         Read the lines of RECORD
 295         """
 296         text = self.read_text('RECORD')
 297         return text and text.splitlines()
 298 
 299     def _read_files_egginfo(self):
 300         """
 301         SOURCES.txt might contain literal commas, so wrap each line
 302         in quotes.
 303         """
 304         text = self.read_text('SOURCES.txt')
 305         return text and map('"{}"'.format, text.splitlines())
 306 
 307     @property
 308     def requires(self):
 309         """Generated requirements specified for this Distribution"""
 310         reqs = self._read_dist_info_reqs() or self._read_egg_info_reqs()
 311         return reqs and list(reqs)
 312 
 313     def _read_dist_info_reqs(self):
 314         return self.metadata.get_all('Requires-Dist')
 315 
 316     def _read_egg_info_reqs(self):
 317         source = self.read_text('requires.txt')
 318         return source and self._deps_from_requires_text(source)
 319 
 320     @classmethod
 321     def _deps_from_requires_text(cls, source):
 322         section_pairs = cls._read_sections(source.splitlines())
 323         sections = {
 324             section: list(map(operator.itemgetter('line'), results))
 325             for section, results in
 326             itertools.groupby(section_pairs, operator.itemgetter('section'))
 327             }
 328         return cls._convert_egg_info_reqs_to_simple_reqs(sections)
 329 
 330     @staticmethod
 331     def _read_sections(lines):
 332         section = None
 333         for line in filter(None, lines):
 334             section_match = re.match(r'\[(.*)\]$', line)
 335             if section_match:
 336                 section = section_match.group(1)
 337                 continue
 338             yield locals()
 339 
 340     @staticmethod
 341     def _convert_egg_info_reqs_to_simple_reqs(sections):
 342         """
 343         Historically, setuptools would solicit and store 'extra'
 344         requirements, including those with environment markers,
 345         in separate sections. More modern tools expect each
 346         dependency to be defined separately, with any relevant
 347         extras and environment markers attached directly to that
 348         requirement. This method converts the former to the
 349         latter. See _test_deps_from_requires_text for an example.
 350         """
 351         def make_condition(name):
 352             return name and 'extra == "{name}"'.format(name=name)
 353 
 354         def parse_condition(section):
 355             section = section or ''
 356             extra, sep, markers = section.partition(':')
 357             if extra and markers:
 358                 markers = '({markers})'.format(markers=markers)
 359             conditions = list(filter(None, [markers, make_condition(extra)]))
 360             return '; ' + ' and '.join(conditions) if conditions else ''
 361 
 362         for section, deps in sections.items():
 363             for dep in deps:
 364                 yield dep + parse_condition(section)
 365

 367 class DistributionFinder(MetaPathFinder):
 368     """
 369     A MetaPathFinder capable of discovering installed distributions.
 370     """
 371 
 372     class Context:
 373         """
 374         Keyword arguments presented by the caller to
 375         ``distributions()`` or ``Distribution.discover()``
 376         to narrow the scope of a search for distributions
 377         in all DistributionFinders.
 378 
 379         Each DistributionFinder may expect any parameters
 380         and should attempt to honor the canonical
 381         parameters defined below when appropriate.
 382         """
 383 
 384         name = None
 385         """
 386         Specific name for which a distribution finder should match.
 387         A name of ``None`` matches all distributions.
 388         """
 389 
 390         def __init__(self, **kwargs):
 391             vars(self).update(kwargs)
 392 
 393         @property
 394         def path(self):
 395             """
 396             The path that a distribution finder should search.
 397 
 398             Typically refers to Python package paths and defaults
 399             to ``sys.path``.
 400             """
 401             return vars(self).get('path', sys.path)
 402 
 403     @abc.abstractmethod
 404     def find_distributions(self, context=Context()):
 405         """
 406         Find distributions.
 407 
 408         Return an iterable of all Distribution instances capable of
 409         loading the metadata for packages matching the ``context``,
 410         a DistributionFinder.Context instance.
 411         """
 412 
 413 
 414 class FastPath:
 415     """
 416     Micro-optimized class for searching a path for
 417     children.
 418     """
 419 
 420     def __init__(self, root):
 421         self.root = root
 422         self.base = os.path.basename(root).lower()
 423 
 424     def joinpath(self, child):
 425         return pathlib.Path(self.root, child)
 426 
 427     def children(self):
 428         with suppress(Exception):
 429             return os.listdir(self.root or '')
 430         with suppress(Exception):
 431             return self.zip_children()
 432         return []
 433 
 434     def zip_children(self):
 435         zip_path = zipp.Path(self.root)
 436         names = zip_path.root.namelist()
 437         self.joinpath = zip_path.joinpath
 438 
 439         return unique_ordered(
 440             child.split(posixpath.sep, 1)[0]
 441             for child in names
 442             )
 443 
 444     def is_egg(self, search):
 445         base = self.base
 446         return (
 447             base == search.versionless_egg_name
 448             or base.startswith(search.prefix)
 449             and base.endswith('.egg'))
 450 
 451     def search(self, name):
 452         for child in self.children():
 453             n_low = child.lower()
 454             if (n_low in name.exact_matches
 455                     or n_low.startswith(name.prefix)
 456                     and n_low.endswith(name.suffixes)
 457                     # legacy case:
 458                     or self.is_egg(name) and n_low == 'egg-info'):
 459                 yield self.joinpath(child)
 460 
 461 
 462 class Prepared:
 463     """
 464     A prepared search for metadata on a possibly-named package.
 465     """
 466     normalized = ''
 467     prefix = ''
 468     suffixes = '.dist-info', '.egg-info'
 469     exact_matches = [''][:0]
 470     versionless_egg_name = ''
 471 
 472     def __init__(self, name):
 473         self.name = name
 474         if name is None:
 475             return
 476         self.normalized = name.lower().replace('-', '_')
 477         self.prefix = self.normalized + '-'
 478         self.exact_matches = [
 479             self.normalized + suffix for suffix in self.suffixes]
 480         self.versionless_egg_name = self.normalized + '.egg'
 481

 483 @install
 484 class MetadataPathFinder(NullFinder, DistributionFinder):
 485     """A degenerate finder for distribution packages on the file system.
 486 
 487     This finder supplies only a find_distributions() method for versions
 488     of Python that do not have a PathFinder find_distributions().
 489     """
 490 
 491     def find_distributions(self, context=DistributionFinder.Context()):
 492         """
 493         Find distributions.
 494 
 495         Return an iterable of all Distribution instances capable of
 496         loading the metadata for packages matching ``context.name``
 497         (or all names if ``None`` indicated) along the paths in the list
 498         of directories ``context.path``.
 499         """
 500         found = self._search_paths(context.name, context.path)
 501         return map(PathDistribution, found)
 502 
 503     @classmethod
 504     def _search_paths(cls, name, paths):
 505         """Find metadata directories in paths heuristically."""
 506         return itertools.chain.from_iterable(
 507             path.search(Prepared(name))
 508             for path in map(FastPath, paths)
 509             )
 510 
 511 
 512 class PathDistribution(Distribution):
 513     def __init__(self, path):
 514         """Construct a distribution from a path to the metadata directory.
 515 
 516         :param path: A pathlib.Path or similar object supporting
 517                      .joinpath(), __div__, .parent, and .read_text().
 518         """
 519         self._path = path
 520 
 521     def read_text(self, filename):
 522         with suppress(FileNotFoundError, IsADirectoryError, KeyError,
 523                       NotADirectoryError, PermissionError):
 524             return self._path.joinpath(filename).read_text(encoding='utf-8')
 525     read_text.__doc__ = Distribution.read_text.__doc__
 526 
 527     def locate_file(self, path):
 528         return self._path.parent / path
 529

 531 def distribution(distribution_name):
 532     """Get the ``Distribution`` instance for the named package.
 533 
 534     :param distribution_name: The name of the distribution package as a string.
 535     :return: A ``Distribution`` instance (or subclass thereof).
 536     """
 537     return Distribution.from_name(distribution_name)

 541     """Get all ``Distribution`` instances in the current environment.

 543     :return: An iterable of ``Distribution`` instances.

 557 def version(distribution_name):
 558     """Get the version string for the named package.
 559 
 560     :param distribution_name: The name of the distribution package to query.
 561     :return: The version string for the package as defined in the package's

 567 def entry_points():
 568     """Return EntryPoint objects for all installed packages.
 569 
 570     :return: EntryPoint objects for all installed packages.
 571     """
 572     eps = itertools.chain.from_iterable(
 573         dist.entry_points for dist in distributions())
 574     by_group = operator.attrgetter('group')
 575     ordered = sorted(eps, key=by_group)
 576     grouped = itertools.groupby(ordered, by_group)
 577     return {
 578         group: tuple(eps)
 579         for group, eps in grouped
 580         }

 584     """Return a list of files for the named package.

 587     :return: List of files composing the distribution.
